      "writtenOn": "2019-06-11T01:01:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e We pass in a ProcessMemory and a ProcessMemoryRange and either of the upstream callers (ProcessSnapshot{Fuchsia,Linux}) actually limit the range object at all. Perhaps we should just use a ProcessMemory since the ModuleSnapshot can also read outside of the modules bounds? Mark do you have an opinion?\n\nThis ProcessMemoryRange is basically just clamping us to 32 bits in 32-bit processes, not restricting to the module image, right?\n\nIt doesn’t seem worth a whole separate parameter for that. ProcessMemory ought to handle this for us.",
