      "writtenOn": "2019-06-11T16:29:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Changing from ProcessMemoryRange to ProcessMemory would require either modifying ImageAnnotationReader to take ProcessMemory (which doesn\u0027t look trivial since it is using the Is64Bit() method), or creating the ProcessMemoryRange inside ModuleSnapshotElf, which would need a is_64_bit param added to the constructor (which doesn\u0027t seem much better than just passing ProcessMemoryRange directly). Is it ok to submit this as-is?",
      "parentUuid": "48beb2cb_25dadaa8",
      "revId": "da388cbf1baa5035f83b30f583b1478304afd42c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
